-------------------------------------------------------------------------

* ifconfig (interface config)

* ip (advanced command of ifconfig)

* netstat (see network statistics) 

* netstat -at (which ports available)

* ss (Same as netstat, give more info) 

* ping host (checks connectivity between two nodes)

* telnet host (create a remote connection with a system)

* nslookup google.com (see DNS details or connection)

* curl (to transfer data to/from server)

* apt-get (handle packages in linux)

* wget URL (gets content)

* scp src dst (copy file from remote server)

* traceroute www.murthi.com (display how data transmitted from local machine to a remote machine)

* tracepath www.murthi.com (same as traceroute, but doesn't require root privileges)

* route (displays and manipulate IP routing table)

